JSE- and NYSE-listed Harmony Gold has appointed Boipelo Lekubo to succeed Frank Abbott as FD, effective March 3. Lekubo, a chartered accountant with extensive experience in group financial management and reporting within the mining industry, has been Harmony's CFO since June 2017. She also served as an independent nonexecutive director of Trans Hex Group from August 2013 until March 2017 and currently serves as an independent nonexecutive director on the boards of African Rainbow Capital and UBI General Partner. Abbott will remain an executive director of Harmony. Harmony chairperson Dr Patrice Motsepe thanked him for his "invaluable contribution" in the role of FD.